          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 226Ra as radium sulfate precipitates were then",
                "deposited by vacuum filtration onto 10 microm thick",
                "track-etched polycarbonate (PCTE) membrane filters",
                "of 0.2 microm porosity (Sterlitech PCT0225100). The",
                "targets contained 810+-85 kBq (21.9+-2.3 microg) of",
                "226Ra deposited on the filtration membrane. The",
                "implied thickness of the 226Ra on the filtration",
                "membrane was 120 microg/cm2, though the thickness was",
                "not measured.",
                "Proton Energy   Target           Initial 226Ra Activity",
                " (MeV)           Identifier      (Bq)",
                "15.1            Target 10        6.51E+05",
                "16.0            Target 11        7.38E+05",
                "16.8            Target 9         7.85E+05"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The principle of the measurement technique is",
                "to quantify decay product activities after",
                "irradiation, relative to the number of beam-target",
                "interactions, as monitored by elastic scattering of",
                "the protons from the radium target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The errors considered in analysis of the",
                "226Ra(p,xn) cross sections include systematic",
                "uncertainties for the technique as well as counting",
                "statistics and fitting uncertainties for each",
                "measurement. Uncertainties assigned to the",
                "226Ra(p,xn) cross section results are obtained by",
                "propagation of the above sources of error. Some, such",
                "as the offline counting statistics for a single",
                "acquisition session, are independent, affecting only",
                "a single result. Others, like the proton peak",
                "integration, affect the values for all isotopes",
                "studied at one energy. Finally, systematic errors in",
                "determining, for example, the proton scattering",
                "detector acceptance aperture, affect the scale of the",
                "entire data set, but do not disturb the internal",
                "consistency of relative cross section comparisons. In",
                "the following summary, absolute uncertainties for",
                "each cross section are estimated, but the relative",
                "errors, for example in the ratio between 224Ac and",
                "225Ac cross sections, may be less and are not",
                "addressed. Combined in quadrature, the above",
                "measurement uncertainties result in overall 1-sigma",
                "uncertainties ranging from 8.2% to 14.9% on the",
                "reaction cross sections."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
